title: Vinci beats Pliskova to reach semifinals of Wuhan Open
text:
Roberta Vinci beats Karolina Pliskova to reach semifinals of Wuhan Open THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   4:45   4:46   
People: 
East Asia (691) 

WUHAN, China — U.S. Open finalist Roberta Vinci beat Karolina Pliskova 7-6 (2), 6-3 to advance to the semifinals of the Wuhan Open on Thursday. 
The 15th-seeded Italian saved three of four break points and took advantage of 30 unforced errors by the eighth-seeded Pliskova. 
Vinci, who has won 10 of her last 11 matches, next faces the winner of the quarterfinal between Venus Williams and Johanna Konta later Thursday. 
Also, fifth-seeded Garbine Muguruza of Spain coasted to a 6-2, 6-2 win over Anna Karolina Schmiedlova. 
Muguruza, who needed just 72 minutes to dispatch her Slovakian opponent, will play either Angelique Kerber or Coco Vandeweghe in Friday's semifinals.
